The -b flag creates a new branch.
git checkout -b &lt;branchname&gt;



git checkout &lt;branchname&gt;



git branch -d &lt;branchname&gt;

Get into groups of 2 or 3.
The product owner should:

create a repository under their account named demo-website (or use your project website!)
add the remaining team members (and me) as collaborators to the repo. This is done under the repo settings
enable github pages on this repo with the main branch as the source

The product owner should create an index.html and a page called our-team/index.html. Commit and push this change directly to the main branch.

